# SatTrack ‚Äî Nuxt 4 Satellite Pass Tracker

## What This App Does
Ham radio satellite pass tracker and AR visualizer. Built with Nuxt 4 as a PWA.

- Pass predictions and polar plot visualization
- Augmented reality tracking using device compass (feature/ar-satellite-tracking branch)
- Transponder frequencies and Doppler correction
- TLE data management
- No calculations ‚Äî everything is delegated to APIs

---

## Tech Stack
- Nuxt 4 (latest) + Vue 3 Composition API + `<script setup>`
- TypeScript strict mode
- UnoCSS (atomic CSS, no Tailwind)
- PWA (installable, offline)
- IndexedDB for encrypted local storage
- No mapping library ‚Äî all visualization is custom SVG/Canvas

---

## APIs

| API | Server proxy | Purpose | Rate limit |
|---|---|---|---|
| N2YO | `server/api/n2yo.post.ts` | Pass predictions + real-time positions | 1000 req/hr (positions/tle), 100/hr (passes) |
| Space-Track | `server/api/space-track.post.ts` | TLE data | ‚Äî |
| CelesTrak | `server/api/celestrak.post.ts` | TLE fallback | ‚Äî |
| SatNOGS | `server/api/satnogs.post.ts` | Transponder frequencies | ‚Äî |
| AMSAT | `server/api/amsat.post.ts` | Amateur frequencies | ‚Äî |

### Space-Track API ‚Äî IMPORTANT
- **Endpoint:** `/basicspacedata/query/class/gp/NORAD_CAT_ID/{ids}/format/json`
- **NEVER use** `tle_latest`, `tle`, or `tle_publish` ‚Äî these are deprecated and return 404
- The `gp` class returns the same fields: `OBJECT_NAME`, `TLE_LINE1`, `TLE_LINE2`
- Constant defined in `constants/api.ts` ‚Üí `API_ENDPOINTS.SPACE_TRACK.TLE`

### N2YO Polar Plot Strategy
N2YO positions endpoint is limited (1000/hr). For the polar plot:
1. Fetch predicted pass path upfront (visualpasses or radiopasses ‚Äî 100/hr limit)
2. Draw the full predicted path as dashed arc on polar plot SVG
3. During active pass only: poll positions every 5-10s for real dot position
4. Cache aggressively ‚Äî reuse pass prediction data across components

